
[1]estivation

   ESTIVA'TION, n. [L. oestivatio, from oestas, summer, oestivo, to pass
   the summer.]

   1. The act of passing the summer.

   2. In botany, the disposition of the petals within the floral gem or
   bud; l. convolute, when the petals are rolled together like a scroll;
   2. imbricate, when they lie over each other like tiles on a roof; 3.
   conduplicate, when they are doubled together at the midrib; 4. valvate,
   when as they are about to expand they are placed like the glumes in
   grasses.
